com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions

Interface Fn1<A,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The argument type
    B - The result type
    All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Effect<A>, Fn0<A>, Fn2<A,B,C>, Fn3<A,B,C,D>, Fn4<A,B,C,D,E>, Fn5<A,B,C,D,E,F>, Fn6<A,B,C,D,E,F,G>, Fn7<A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H>, Fn8<A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,I>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Fn1<A,B>
extends com.jnape.palatable.lambda.monad.Monad<B,Fn1<A,?>>, com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Cartesian<A,B,Fn1<?,?>>, com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Cocartesian<A,B,Fn1<?,?>>
    A function taking a single argument. This is the core function type that all other function types extend and auto-curry with.
